{
  "title": "DMA Audit Report: Search Ranking for 'batteries'",
  "extracted_receipts_summary": "The inspection analyzed 10 search suggestions/results generated for the generic keyword 'batteries'. All recorded entries were explicitly categorized as originating from 'third_party' entities. There is no evidence within this sample set (top 10 results) of proprietary products or services belonging to the gatekeeper undertaking being injected or given preferential visibility.",
  "dma_compliance_mapping": "The analysis primarily addresses compliance with DMA Article 6(5), which prohibits self-preferencing in ranking. The provided receipts show 10 consecutive third-party results, indicating that, for this specific generic keyword, the gatekeeper is not visibly prioritizing its own similar products (e.g., house brands of batteries) in the top search suggestions. This structure suggests initial compliance with the non-discrimination requirements regarding ranking. However, this observation is limited to the visibility layer; a full assessment of Article 6(5) requires inspecting the neutrality of the underlying indexing and crawling processes.",
  "risk_assessment": "Low. Based strictly on the visual evidence provided in the receipts, there is no immediate indication of a violation of Article 6(5) (Self-Preferencing). All observed results are correctly categorized as third-party, suggesting the platform's compliance mechanisms related to ranking visibility are effective for this type of generic search query."
}

